<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/732</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                                (<hi rend="italic">White</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-11">January 11, 1933</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Brazilian Ambassador telephoned to say that he was instructed by his
                            Government to express the thanks of the Brazilian Government for our
                            support in Lima of the Brazilian proposal.</p>
                        <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps">hite</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>